<subSubSection id="86D74AC4353CFFEF199ADAB166D8F815" pageId="2" pageNumber="455" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CE72194F353CFFEF199ADAB166D8F815" blockId="2.[151,1436,1966,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="455">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353CFFEF199ADAB16555F838" bold="true" box="[199,334,1966,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="455">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named to honour the 
<collectingRegion id="0C09D7AD353CFFEF1BB6DAB1672FF838" box="[747,820,1966,1991]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="2" pageNumber="455">Muğla</collectingRegion>
Sitki Koçman University (
<collectingCountry id="B6DA59DF353CFFEF1D39DAB160A1F838" box="[1124,1210,1966,1991]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="455">Turkey</collectingCountry>
), because most 
<typeStatus id="1176A7ED353CFFEF1C31DAB06187F838" box="[1388,1436,1967,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="455">type</typeStatus>
specimens were captured on its beautiful campus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
