</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86D74AC4353DFFEE199ADDA3616CFE9A" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CE72194F353DFFEE199ADDA3616CFE9A" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE199ADDA36520FF2A" bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species described above is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE1AD8DDA260D0FF2B" authority="(Corti, 1907)" authorityName="Corti" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Corti" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[901,1227,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longimanus">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE1AD8DDA26033FF2A" box="[901,1064,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. longimanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AA5C64BE353DFFEE1D61DDA360DFFF2B" box="[1084,1220,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" refId="ref22207" refString="Corti, E. (1907) Eine neue Art der Dipterengattung Tachydromia (Mg.) Lw. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 26, 101 - 102." type="journal article">Corti, 1907</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE1C56DDA2664CFF07" authority="Grootaert, Kustov &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert, Kustov &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="negrobovi">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE1C56DDA26187FF2A" box="[1291,1436,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. negrobovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AA5C64BE353DFFEE19CADDFF664CFF07" box="[151,599,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" refId="ref22744" refString="Grootaert, P., Kustov, S. &amp; Shamshev, I. (2012) Platypalpus negrobovi a new species of the family Hybotidae (Diptera: Empidoidea) from the North-West Caucasus. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 8, 161 - 163." type="journal article">Grootaert, Kustov &amp; Shamshev, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. With microtrichose anepimeron and short stylus, the newly described species is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE18E3DC1A6645FEE2" baseAuthorityName="Corti" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[446,606,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longimanus">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE18E3DC1A6645FEE2" box="[446,606,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. longimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with long apical segment of mid tarsus it reminds us of 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE1C55DC1A618FFEE2" authorityName="Grootaert, Kustov &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[1288,1428,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="negrobovi">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE1C55DC1A618FFEE2" box="[1288,1428,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. negrobovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it differs from both by differently shaped left epandrial lamella (not excised apically) and much narrower (and not strikingly sexually dimorphic as in 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE1BDBDC52673EFE9A" baseAuthorityName="Corti" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[646,805,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longimanus">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE1BDBDC52673EFE9A" box="[646,805,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. longimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) stylus in male (female of 
<taxonomicName id="09CD62CC353DFFEE1D0FDC5260C6FE9A" authorityName="Grootaert, Kustov &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[1106,1245,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="negrobovi">
<emphasis id="FCB9C55D353DFFEE1D0FDC5260C6FE9A" box="[1106,1245,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="456">P. negrobovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
